@muhtarc4n, you can install packages from GitHub by specifying them in your `requirements.txt` too. See the docs of `pip`, especially the part about [Requirements Files](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/user_guide/#requirements-files):

> For example, suppose a dependency, SomeDependency from PyPI has a bug, and you can't wait for an upstream fix. [..]

You might also have a look at the supported forms when [installing from Git](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/?highlight=vcs#git).

