In the same time in tests this situation is expectable: https://github.com/pytries/marisa-trie/blob/master/tests/test_bytes_trie.py#L106.

By the way I understood why this happens:
For Trie class everything is perfect. For BytesTrie and others inherited from him in constructor pairs `(key, value)` transform to `new_key = key + separator + value`.  Inside the methods keys/iterkeys you iterate over set of new_keys and then cut old key back.
```python
for i in range(0, ag.key().length()):
  if raw_key[i] == self._c_value_separator:
    key = raw_key[:i].decode('utf8')
```
And then you add the same key to the `res` several times.

